     <h2 id="hd_id641641501024846">Editing read-Only contents</h2>
     <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id841641501075965">If you try to edit protected sections, a warning message will be displayed and no modifications will be made to the section.</paragraph>
     <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id531641501248838">To remove protection of a section, do the following:</paragraph>
     <list type="ordered">
     <listitem>
         <paragraph id="par_id681641501272982" role="listitem">Go to <menuitem>Format - Sections</menuitem>.</paragraph>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
         <paragraph id="par_id861641501273184" role="listitem">In the <menuitem>Section</menuitem> area of the dialog, choose which section you wish to unprotect.</paragraph>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
         <paragraph id="par_id221641501273326" role="listitem">Uncheck the <menuitem>Protect</menuitem>  option in the <menuitem>Write Protection</menuitem>  area of the dialog.</paragraph>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
         <paragraph id="par_id791641501273494" role="listitem">Enter the password used to protect the document into the dialog that will open.</paragraph>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
         <paragraph id="par_id561641501273767" role="listitem">Click <menuitem>OK</menuitem> .</paragraph>
       </listitem>
     </list>

